race.description: In Memory Of Ray Webber Handicap (Bm58)
race.comment: HIBIKI HARMONY (1) has been going well for some time now in better races than this. Led for home and tried very hard but was ambushed near the line last start in a BM66 over 1450m here. Beautifully placed to take this out despite the 61kgs. DREYMON (7) wasn't suited dropping back in trip last time out and failed to feature over 1206m at Port Macquarie. Raced here once at this distance and filled a minor placing. Well placed to run a much better race this time. FLEETLY (8) appreciated the drop in grade when runner-up in a BM50 at Mudgee recently. Very fit after three runs back and should now measure up in this company. SHADOW DANE (3) won a Class 2 first-up in heavy going but has been plain in two subsequent runs on good tracks. On an eight-day back-up and might be worth including in exotics. SANZENO (2) didn't fire when resuming at Tamworth but is better placed out to this distance.
